        public void close()
        Description copied from interface: Transaction
        Closes the Transaction. Resources may be freed. Upon normal completion, the state will be Closed. Close cannot be called while posting. Once closed, the Transaction must not support any activity.

      • post

        public final void post()
        Description copied from interface: Transaction
        Posts changes managed by this Transaction (optional operation). A Transaction supports 1 post. Changes required after a post must be performed through a new Transaction. The Transaction.Status is POSTING while this method is executing. Upon completion, the status will be POSTED or FAILED.
        Specified by:
        post in interface Transaction
